cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with unsupervised learning for identifying anomalies in imaging data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses a deep convolutional generative adversarial network (GAN), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of anomaly detection for guiding marker discovery, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of GANs for anomaly detection is a relatively new area of research, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to optical coherence tomography images of the retina, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
